Collections.frequency gives you occurrences of an object in a list.
 
Another option since this is a small array is to sort it and then iterate, and in the case where `array[i+1] == array[i]`, increase the count of duplicate values.

If elements in this case is not a primitive type, remember to overload the operator.

sample implementation:

    void countOcc(int []arr) {	
    	Set&lt;Integer&gt; uniques = new LinkedHashSet&lt;Integer&gt;();
    	for(int x : arr) {
    		uniques.add(x);
    	}
    		
    	for(int y : uniques) {
    		int totalOcc = Collections.frequency(Arrays.asList(arr), y);
    		//gives total occurences for each unique element in the array
    	}
    }

