Because JMS messages are serialized in sending process, the best way how to obtain size of message is [through ObjectOutputStream](https://stackoverflow.com/a/52362/600132).

    private int getMessageSizeInBytes(MessageWrapper message) throws IOException {
        ByteArrayOutputStream baos = new ByteArrayOutputStream();
        ObjectOutputStream oos = new ObjectOutputStream(baos);
        oos.writeObject(message);
        oos.close();
        return baos.size();
    }

